ENUGU – Zikist-Buharist Movement (ZBM), South East zone, has applauded the governor of Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN), Godwin Emefiele, for the apex bank’s new policy, reducing all bank charges. ZBM also commended Emefiele and his team for Anchor Borrowers programme, revival of palm oil and textile, among other intervention programmes they embarked upon to diversify the economy and reduce frightening inequality in our dear country. Some of the bank charges got more than 50 percent cut in the new CBN policy which takes effect from January 2020. Reacting to the development in a statement, Secretary of ZBM, Godwin Onwusi, described the new policy on bank charges as timely and in line with the vision of President Muhammadu Buhari to lift millions of Nigerians out of poverty. According to Onwusi, the policy has relieved Nigerians of the burden of obnoxious and suffocating charges by commercial banks. Onwusi said the policy would leverage on cashless policy further improves ease of doing business and create more favourable investment climate in the country.